*gaim-otr-3.0.0-r2 (21 Oct 2006)

  21 Oct 2006; gothgirl <gothgirl@gentoo.org> +files/gaim-2b4-otr.patch,
  +gaim-otr-3.0.0-r2.ebuild:
  Revision bump to work with gaim-2.0beta4

*gaim-otr-3.0.0-r1 (14 Jun 2006)

  14 Jun 2006; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> +gaim-otr-3.0.0-r1.ebuild:
  Apply upstream patch to allow building against GAIM 2 beta releases as
  suggested by Joshua Schmidlkofer <menion@asylumwear.com> in bug #127240.

*gaim-otr-3.0.0 (14 Nov 2005)

  14 Nov 2005; Don Seiler <rizzo@gentoo.org> +gaim-otr-3.0.0.ebuild:
  Version bump for bug #111645

  01 Aug 2005; Joseph Jezak <josejx@gentoo.org> gaim-otr-2.0.2.ebuild:
  Marked ~ppc for bug #100396.

  10 Jul 2005; Sven Wegener <swegener@gentoo.org> gaim-otr-1.0.3.ebuild,
  gaim-otr-2.0.0.ebuild, gaim-otr-2.0.1.ebuild, gaim-otr-2.0.2.ebuild:
  QA: Removed 'emake || make || die' and variants. Either a package is
  parallel build safe or it is not. There's nothing like trying and falling
  back.

